<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>shoot the crow • stone the crows</xh5><p> <i>shoot the crow</i>—(sl.) 1. depart hurriedly; make off: There’ll only be his mother in the house. His father <u>shot the crow</u> years ago. 2. sneak off without paying: A canny Scot was sentenced to ten days’ hard for <u>shooting the crow</u>—ordering whiskey and neglecting to pay.</p><p><i>stone the crows</i>—(sl., also: stone me) is used as an exclamation of surprise, etc.: “<u>Stone the Crows</u>!,” shouted Peter Grant, when he first heard this splendid young Scottish band roaring into action.</p> </entry>
